To the surfers, dog-walkers, achar-sellers, buyers of black-market cigarettes, and braai-brigades, I salute you. Because with you, I am prepared to fight this war against Covid 19. Unfortunately, in this war, we, the people of South Africa, have all been taken prisoner. It’s called a lockdown but, in reality, we are locked up with uniformed, armed soldiers ensuring we remain behind our own burglar bars and steel gates, only allowed out for our daily exercise. We are also rationed with what we are allowed to buy and consume. And on top of this, we are rationed with information – effectively...